ST5 flap (
Fig. 50
) longer than broad, with a deep marginal excavation almost reaching halfway to its base, and with diverging lateral edges.

Distiphallus short and high, almost triangular in profile view. Projecting dorsolateral wings absent; middorsal wall broad, fused with vertical sclerotised sheet (
Figs. 47, 51
). Antlers rather short and projecting upwards and forwards, grooved on anterior side. No basal tooth present. Upper lip (
Fig. 47
, upper arrow) not projecting beyond base of antlers in dorsal view. [The mid-dorsal wall is ruptured along the midline in the only available genital preparation, rupture seen in 
Figs. 47, 51
]. Lateral finger large (
Figs. 45, 51, 52
), spinose distally. Vertical sclerotised sheet very conspicuous and its anterior edge smooth, slightly concave, as seen in lateral view. Internal hypophallic lobes strongly converging as seen in ventral view. External hypophallic lobes folded in anterior part, presenting a forwardly facing wall, which is well sclerotised laterally, and which backwards (
Fig. 47
) and also inwards (
Figs. 45, 51
). Each parastomal sclerite has a small dorsal projection basally (
Fig. 51
).
